South Korean Finance Minister ChungIn-yong will resist pressure for a currency revaluation to cutSouth Korea's trade surplus with the United States when hemeets Treasury Secretary James Baker next week, FinanceMinistry officials said.    They said Chung would leave Monday to attend theInternational Monetary Fund's Interim Committee meeting and tohold talks with Baker and other U.S. officials on ways toreduce the surplus.    The April 9 committee meeting is expected to review theagreement by six industrialized nations in Paris last monththat newly-industrialized countries, such as South Korea andTaiwan, should allow their currencies to increase in value. Reuter&#3;